'''Kiran Shah''' (born [[September 28]], [[1950s#1956|1956]], in [[Wikipedia:Kenya|Kenya]])<ref name="CNN" /> is a 4&prime;2&Prime; actor and stuntman who played the [[Ewok]] [[Brethupp]] and many stunt Ewoks, and the [[Unidentified power droid (Jabba's Palace)|tortured power droid]] in [[Star Wars: Episode VI Return of the Jedi|''Return of the Jedi'']],<ref name="Kiran Shah" /> after originally being only called on for the fitting of the original Ewok costumes.<ref name="CNN" /> He returned to ''[[Star Wars]]'' in the 2010s. He played [[Infrablue Zedbeddy Coggins]], [[Pru Sweevant]],<ref name="Kiran Shah" /> and [[Teedo (Niima Outpost)|Teedo]]<ref name="TFA">{{Film|VII}}</ref> in [[Star Wars: Episode VII The Force Awakens|''The Force Awakens'']]; and [[Neepers Panpick]] in [[Star Wars: Episode VIII The Last Jedi|''The Last Jedi'']].<ref name="TLJ">{{Film|VIII}}</ref> For ''[[Rogue One: A Star Wars Story]]'' Shah worked as a creature and [[droid]] performer<ref name="Kiran Shah" /> and played the [[Blutopian]] [[Oolin Musters]],<ref name="Much to Learn">{{SW|url=news/much-to-learn-you-still-have-talking-rogue-one-aliens-with-pablo-hidalgo|text=Much to Learn You Still Have: Talking ''Rogue One'' Aliens with Pablo Hidalgo}}</ref> and played [[Karjj]] in ''[[Solo: A Star Wars Story]]''.<ref name="Instagram">{{Instagram|username=jakeluntdavies|url=p/BhFRp6cljsy|name=[[Jake Lunt Davies]]|date=2018-04-02|archiveurl=https://archive.is/9Cw1a}}</ref><ref name="Kiran Shah" /> In [[Star Wars: Episode IX The Rise of Skywalker|''The Rise of Skywalker'']], he plays the [[Aki-Aki]] [[Nambi Ghima]], the mechanic [[Yipsit]]<ref name="TROS">{{Film|IX}}</ref> and a [[GNK-series power droid]].<ref name="Kiran Shah" /> Shah worked as a puppeteer on the [[Disney+]] television series ''[[Star Wars: Andor]]'', where he portrayed the character [[Granik]]<ref name="Shah Andor2">{{SW|url=andor-s1-e2-trivia-gallery|text="That Would Be Me" Trivia Gallery &#124; Andor}}</ref> and a sleeping Blutopian.<ref name="Kiran Shah" />

Since [[2003]], Shah has held the [[Wikipedia:Guinness World Records|Guinness World Record]] as the "shortest professional stuntman currently working in film."<ref name="Guiness">{{WebCite|url=https://www.guinnessworldrecords.com/world-records/shortest-stuntman|text=Shortest stuntman|work=[[Wikipedia:Guinness World Records|Guinness World Records]]|archivedate=20240705021619}}</ref> Shah's many film credits include [[Wikipedia:Raiders of the Lost Ark|''Raiders of the Lost Ark'']],<ref name="Shah Andor2" /> [[Wikipedia:The Dark Crystal|''The Dark Crystal'']], the villainous dwarf [[W:c:Narnia:Ginarrbrik|Ginarrbrik]] in [[Wikipedia:The Chronicles of Narnia: The Lion, the Witch and the Wardrobe|''The Chronicles of Narnia: The Lion, the Witch and the Wardrobe'']], and the [[Wikipedia:The Lord of the Rings film trilogy|''Lord of the Rings'']] trilogy (where he was [[Wikipedia:Elijah Wood|Elijah Wood]]'s scale double as [[Wikipedia:Frodo Baggins|Frodo Baggins]]).<ref name="CNN" />

